Calcular la regla de Bayes¶

P(A)=a P(B)=b P(A|B)=c P(B|A)=d P(B|NA)=e

In [43]:
def bayes(a, d, e):
    na = 1 - a
    b = d * a + e * na
    c = (d * a) / b
    return c
 
# P(A)
a = 0.25
# P(B|A)
d = 0.75
# P(B|NA)
e = 0.37

# calcular P(A|B)
r = bayes(a, d, e)
print('P(A|B) = %.4f%%' % (r))

P(A|B) = 0.4032%
